Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Full Stack Game Engineer* with *Scopely*. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack engineering, cloud-native backend systems, and high-performance interactive applications, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across three engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect *the technical depth and architectural complexity of live game systems*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system that handles scalable automated actions across complex client/server workflows — requiring rigorous API design and safe execution across a distributed surface, mirroring the complexity of Pokémon GO’s real-time interactions. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented a full observability stack using LangSmith for tracing and evaluation, reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and ensuring high responsiveness for interactive services. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that seamlessly handled file operations across AWS S3 and Google Cloud Storage — giving me direct, hands-on experience with the *GCP* environment and cloud-native backend design central to this role. I also built robust backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to handle long-running data jobs, ensuring operational stability and system reliability — both of which are critical for supporting *the end-to-end game systems and live operations this position demands*. Together, these roles have prepared me to *contribute meaningfully to the development of gameplay features and supporting backend services* at Scopely.

My academic research and leadership experience have given me a rigorous foundation in GPU-accelerated computing and technical communication — skills that translate directly into *the engineering discipline and "Iterate to Greatness" culture Scopely values*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on generative models, leveraging CUDA and PyTorch on an HPC cluster for high-performance inference deployment. Managing the full development lifecycle — from model training to vLLM-optimized serving — ensured I could deliver low-latency performance in high-concurrency environments. Beyond technical implementation, I led workshops on GPU programming and building AI Agents for 50+ students, demonstrating my ability to break down complex technical concepts clearly. This experience directly mirrors *the mentorship, code review participation, and collaborative knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to this role*. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to *the Pokémon GO team and Scopely’s mission*.

I have always been passionate about Scopely’s commitment to *"Inspire play, every day"* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *creating meaningful connections and making life better through play*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

